---
import Layout from "@layouts/ClientLayout.astro";

---

<Layout description="Acceptance of Terms we use" title="terms & conditions " keywords={["terms","conditions of use"]}>
    
<main class="container-sm">

    <h1>Terms and Conditions of [Your Platform Name]</h1>

    <p>Welcome to [Your Platform Name]! By accessing or using our website and services, you agree to comply with and be bound by the following terms and conditions. Please read them carefully.</p>

    <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms:</h2>

    <p>By using [Your Platform Name], you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to be bound by these Terms. If you do not agree with any part of these Terms, you must not use our services.</p>

    <h2>2. Use of the Platform:</h2>

    <ul>
        <li><strong>Eligibility:</strong> You must be at least 18 years of age and legally capable of entering into binding contracts to use our platform. Hosts must also provide valid identification and proof of property ownership or management authority.</li>
        <li><strong>Account Creation:</strong> You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account information, including your password. You agree to notify us immediately of any unauthorized access to your account.</li>
        <li><strong>Accuracy of Information:</strong> You agree to provide accurate, current, and complete information when creating a listing or making a booking. Any misrepresentation may result in the suspension or termination of your account.</li>
        <li><strong>Prohibited Activities:</strong> You agree not to engage in any illegal, fraudulent, or harmful activities on our platform. This includes, but is not limited to:
            <ul>
                <li>Posting false or misleading information.</li>
                <li>Attempting to circumvent our booking and payment systems.</li>
                <li>Distributing malware or other harmful software.</li>
                <li>Harassing or threatening other users.</li>
                <li>Engaging in any activity that violates applicable laws and regulations.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Booking and Payments:</h2>

    <ul>
        <li><strong>Booking Confirmation:</strong> A booking is confirmed when you receive a confirmation email from [Your Platform Name] and payment has been successfully processed.</li>
        <li><strong>Payment:</strong> You agree to pay the total amount specified for your booking, including any applicable taxes, fees, and security deposits. We may use third-party payment processors, and you agree to their terms and conditions.</li>
        <li><strong>Cancellation Policy:</strong> Cancellation policies vary by listing and are determined by the host. Please review the specific cancellation policy before booking. [Your Platform Name] may charge a service fee for cancellations.</li>
        <li><strong>Security Deposit:</strong> Some listings may require a security deposit to cover potential damages. The deposit will be refunded after your stay, subject to deductions for damages as determined by the host and [Your Platform Name].</li>
        <li><strong>Funds Handling:</strong> [Your Platform Name] acts as an intermediary for payment processing. Funds are held securely until the booking is completed, subject to our dispute resolution policy.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Host Responsibilities:</h2>

    <ul>
        <li><strong>Eligibility:</strong> Hosts must meet specific eligibility criteria, including providing valid identification and proof of property ownership or management authority.</li>
        <li><strong>Listing Accuracy:</strong> Hosts are responsible for ensuring the accuracy of their listings, including descriptions, photos, amenities, and availability. Any discrepancies may result in penalties.</li>
        <li><strong>Property Maintenance:</strong> Hosts are responsible for maintaining their properties in a safe, clean, and habitable condition. This includes adhering to all applicable safety and health regulations.</li>
        <li><strong>Guest Communication:</strong> Hosts are expected to communicate promptly and professionally with guests, responding to inquiries and addressing concerns in a timely manner.</li>
        <li><strong>Compliance:</strong> Hosts must comply with all applicable laws and regulations, including zoning laws, tax regulations, and safety standards.</li>
        <li><strong>Availability Calendar:</strong> Hosts must keep their availability calendar up to date and accurate. Failure to do so may result in booking conflicts and penalties.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Guest Responsibilities:</h2>

    <ul>
        <li><strong>Property Rules:</strong> Guests agree to abide by the rules set by the host, as specified in the listing.</li>
        <li><strong>Property Condition:</strong> Guests are responsible for leaving the property in the same condition as when they arrived, reasonable wear and tear excepted.</li>
        <li><strong>Damage:</strong> Guests are responsible for any damage they cause to the property, and may be required to pay for repairs or replacements.</li>
        <li><strong>Check-In/Check-Out:</strong> Guests agree to adhere to the check-in and check-out times specified by the host.</li>
        <li><strong>Respectful Conduct:</strong> Guests are expected to conduct themselves respectfully towards hosts, neighbors, and other guests.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. Reviews and Ratings:</h2>

    <ul>
        <li><strong>Accuracy:</strong> Reviews and ratings must be honest, accurate, and based on personal experiences.</li>
        <li><strong>Prohibited Content:</strong> You agree not to post any offensive, defamatory, or inappropriate content in your reviews.</li>
        <li><strong>Moderation:</strong> [Your Platform Name] reserves the right to remove or edit reviews that violate these Terms or our community guidelines.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>7. Intellectual Property:</h2>

    <ul>
        <li><strong>Ownership:</strong> [Your Platform Name] owns all content on the platform, including text, images, logos, and software.</li>
        <li><strong>Use:</strong> You agree not to use our content without our express written permission, except as permitted for personal, non-commercial use.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>8. Limitation of Liability:</h2>

    <ul>
        <li><strong>Disclaimer:</strong> [Your Platform Name] is not responsible for any damages or losses incurred by users, including but not limited to property damage, personal injury, or financial loss.</li>
        <li><strong>Indemnification:</strong> You agree to indemnify and hold [Your Platform Name] harmless from any claims or liabilities arising from your use of the platform.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>9. Data Privacy:</h2>

    <ul>
        <li><strong>Data Collection:</strong> We collect and use your personal information in accordance with our Privacy Policy. Please review our Privacy Policy for details on how we collect, use, and protect your data.</li>
        <li><strong>Data Security:</strong> We implement reasonable security measures to protect your data, but we cannot guarantee absolute security.</li>
        <li><strong>Data Sharing:</strong> We may share your data with third-party service providers as necessary to provide our services.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>10. Scams and Fraud Prevention:</h2>

    <ul>
        <li><strong>Reporting:</strong> Users are encouraged to report any suspected scams or fraudulent activity to [Your Platform Name] immediately.</li>
        <li><strong>Verification:</strong> We may implement verification procedures to prevent fraud, including identity verification and property verification.</li>
        <li><strong>Liability:</strong> [Your Platform Name] is not liable for any losses resulting from scams or fraudulent activity.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>11. Changes to Terms:</h2>

    <ul>
        <li><strong>Modification:</strong> [Your Platform Name] reserves the right to modify these Terms at any time.</li>
        <li><strong>Notification:</strong> We will notify you of any changes by posting the updated Terms on our website or through other means of communication.</li>
        <li><strong>Acceptance:</strong> Your continued use of our services constitutes acceptance of the updated Terms.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>12. Governing Law:</h2>

    <ul>
        <li><strong>Jurisdiction:</strong> These Terms are governed by the laws of [Your Jurisdiction].</li>
        <li><strong>Disputes:</strong> Any disputes will be resolved in the courts of [Your Jurisdiction].</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>13. Contact Us:</h2>

    <p>If you have any questions about these Terms, please contact us at [Your Contact Information].</p>

    <h2>Appendix: Specific Booking Policies</h2>

    <ul>
        <li><strong>Long-Term Stays:</strong> Special terms may apply to stays exceeding 30 days. Please contact us for details.</li>
        <li><strong>Short-Term Stays:</strong> Normal booking policies apply.</li>
        <li><strong>Force Majeure:</strong> We are not responsible for cancellations or disruptions caused by events beyond our control.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Appendix: Host Guidelines</h2>

    <ul>
        <li><strong>Listing Verification:</strong> [Your Platform Name] may verify listings to ensure accuracy and quality.</li>
        <li><strong>Response Time:</strong> Hosts are expected to respond to guest inquiries within [Specified Timeframe].</li>
        <li><strong>Safety Standards:</strong> Hosts must adhere to safety standards outlined by [Your Platform Name].</li>
        <li><strong>Taxes:</strong> Hosts are responsible for collecting and remitting any applicable taxes.</li>
    </ul>

</main>
</Layout>

